Commentary: bowled him, poor stroke from Soumya, and a fantastic innings comes to an end on 149. Length ball straightening towards off stump in the air, and then nipping back slightly off the deck. It's a lazy shot, perhaps looking for the single to get to 150. Looks to flick, plays across the line, and misses, and the ball clips his back pad and knocks back off stump. There was a split second's silence before Boult roared in celebration - it was almost as if he couldn't believe the partnership had ended, finally
